    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-21T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-21T01:00:00-05:00" n="693"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-21T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 21, 1930—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 21—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>353. Department’s 165, May 13, 6 p.m. Following telegram has been received from
                    the Minister: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“May 19, 5 p.m. I have informed the Foreign Office that regulations
                            cannot be regarded as applicable pending receipt of instructions from
                            the Department.”<note n="87" xml:id="d693fn87">The Chinese Ministry for
                                Foreign Affairs in a note dated May 23, 1930, informed the Minister
                                in China of the promulgation of revised regulations, a copy of which
                                was enclosed (893.113/1256).</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
